techmeme.title: Analysis: Intel's stock, up 28% in August, is trading at a 53 forward P/E ratio, its highest since early 2002, reflecting its declining profits in recent years (Ryan Vlastelica/Bloomberg)

Butterfly Effect, the startup behind Manus and an earlier product called Monica, says its annual revenue run rate has hit $90M, with Manus contributing the most (Bloomberg)
PE firm Advent International agrees to acquire U-blox, a SIX Swiss Exchange-listed wireless and positioning chipmaker, for about $1.3B via public tender offer (Andrea Figueras/Wall Street Journal)
Canva debuts a staff stock sale to new and existing investors at a $42B valuation, up 30%+ from $32B in 2024, and reports $3.3B+ annualized sales and 240M+ MAUs (Olivia Poh/Bloomberg)
